# Component Patterns

## Section Components (`navPages/`)

- One file per portfolio section; export a named component (e.g. `export function Projects`)
- Add `id` attributes matching navbar hash links (`id="projects"`, `scroll-mt-28` for offset)
- Mark `"use client"` only when using hooks, Framer Motion, or browser APIs

## Global Client Shell

Heavy or browser-only UI lives in `ClientShell` — not in `layout.tsx`. Load with `dynamic(..., { ssr: false })`:

```tsx
const BackgroundParticles = dynamic(
  () => import("@/components/ui/BackgroundParticles"),
  { ssr: false }
);
```

Applies to: particles, custom cursor, preloader, scroll progress, scroll-to-top.

## Code Splitting on Main Page

`app/page.tsx` lazy-loads below-the-fold sections with `dynamic()`. Keep `Home` eager; defer Experience, Projects, Footer, etc.

## UI Primitives

- shadcn/ui components live in `components/ui/` (New York style, Lucide icons)
- Merge classes with `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` — never raw string concatenation
- Icons: prefer `lucide-react`; use `react-icons` only where already established

## Navbar & Navigation

- Internal section links use `/#section` hash URLs
- Blog routes use `next/link` with pathname-aware logo behavior (see `Navbar.tsx`)
